First of all, I have learnt about:
- Variables: Built-in: $CI_COMMIT_BRANCH, $CI_JOB_STAGE, $CI_PROJECT_DIR, Custom variables: defined in YAML and UI, Masked/Protected variables for secrets:
-- https://pradappandiyan.medium.com/understanding-gitlab-ci-cd-variables-for-pip-c0ef42eef37c;
-- https://docs.gitlab.com/ci/variables/ (Define a CI/CD variable in the UI, CI/CD variable security);
-Environments & Deployments: environment: keyword → defines deploy target (staging/prod), on_stop: → rollback or manual stop job, Environment URLs:
-- https://docs.gitlab.com/ci/environments/;
-- https://docs.gitlab.com/ci/yaml/#environmenton_stop;
- Rules vs. only/except: Rules vs. only/except: rules: allows complex conditions (if: logic) (generated by ChatGPT);
- Parallel jobs: parallel: key for matrix buildsm How GitLab handles concurrent runners (generated by ChatGPT).

